Build a production-quality local web application: a real-time Kubernetes/OpenShift log explorer designed for developers.

The tool should feel like a hybrid between Kibana, VSCode DevTools, and a modern real-time observability SaaS (like Datadog logs UI) — but lightweight, local, and built only on "oc logs".

The UX MUST be modern, clean, and highly polished, with strong emphasis on readability, hierarchy, and fast debugging.

---

🧱 Tech Stack

Frontend

- React (Vite)
- TypeScript
- TailwindCSS (modern design system)
- shadcn/ui (ALL UI components)
- Zustand (state management)
- react-window (virtualized log rendering)
- WebSocket client

Design System (CRITICAL)

- Must use a modern SaaS UI style
- Clean spacing, generous padding
- Soft borders, subtle shadows
- Dark mode first (default)
- High contrast for logs readability
- No cluttered UI

Typography (MANDATORY)

- Use a highly readable font stack:

font-family: Inter, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, Segoe UI, Roboto;

- Monospace for raw logs:

font-family: JetBrains Mono, Fira Code, monospace;

- Ensure:
  - clear line spacing
  - no dense text blocks
  - strong hierarchy (title > filter > logs)

---

Backend

- Node.js (LTS)
- Express (minimal API layer)
- ws (WebSocket server)
- child_process.spawn ("oc logs")
- No external logging infrastructure

